breakfast cereals any more.

39:10.725 --> 39:11.976
I dried your things out.

39:12.477 --> 39:14.479
Thanks. Did I puke?

39:14.688 --> 39:15.772
Nope.

39:18.316 --> 39:19.693
Your house is dead tidy.

39:20.276 --> 39:23.029
Ours always looks like a bomb's
gone off when Dad's away.

39:23.571 --> 39:25.907
Then I guess you haven't got
anyone to make it messy, though.

39:27.951 --> 39:30.328
I suppose keeping it tidy
gives me something to do.

39:31.913 --> 39:33.498
So you don't think about him?

39:36.418 --> 39:38.628
They think we don't know
when people die, but we do.

39:39.462 --> 39:41.589
Like, everyone at school
talks about it.

39:42.424 --> 39:45.468
- They talk about Jamie?
- They talked about you more.

39:49.973 --> 39:51.349
Is that Jamie's car outside?

39:51.433 --> 39:52.726
No, it's mine.

40:01.317 --> 40:02.610
Ah, hi, Frankie.

40:03.528 --> 40:05.989
Right, are we ready to go
into the den and play a game?

40:06.239 --> 40:09.409
Shall we go? OK, right. Take your
book and I'll see you in a minute.

40:10.577 --> 40:13.288
Oi, what are you doing?
You about to take a biscuit?

40:13.371 --> 40:15.665
Go on. Go inside,
we're gonna play a game together.

40:15.749 --> 40:17.834
- You minding kids?
- Do you want to go inside?

40:17.917 --> 40:21.046
I asked her. I hope that's OK.
They are a bit of a distraction.

40:21.129 --> 40:24.090
She's going to do it tomorrow as well
while we go for a hike on the moors.

40:24.174 --> 40:25.258
Right.

40:27.385 --> 40:29.971
Is that Kate's punishment
for you getting pissed last night?

40:31.264 --> 40:32.599
We need to talk about that,
by the way.

40:33.391 --> 40:34.559
Whatever.

40:34.642 --> 40:36.144
No, I'm serious. Where were you?

40:36.686 --> 40:37.687
I was just out.

40:38.271 --> 40:39.272
Frankie!

40:39.356 --> 40:41.191
What? You all get
pissed all the time

40:41.274 --> 40:43.109
cos there's nothing to do,
why shouldn't I?

40:49.449 --> 40:50.825
I said no sheet music.

40:51.743 --> 40:53.453
Right, everyone up.

40:54.037 --> 40:55.246
Here's your starting note.

40:55.580 --> 40:58.500
I'm gonna count us in. Three, four...

40:58.583 --> 41:00.710
<i>Shout, shout</i>

41:00.794 --> 41:02.545
<i>Let it all out</i>

41:02.921 --> 41:06.675
<i>These are the things
I can do without</i>

41:06.758 --> 41:07.759
<i>Come on</i>

41:07.842 --> 41:08.968
Louder.

41:09.260 --> 41:11.805
<i>I'm talking to you, come on</i>

41:11.888 --> 41:12.931
Come on, let rip!

41:13.014 --> 41:15.558
<i>In violent times</i>

41:16.226 --> 41:19.062
<i>You shouldn't have to sell your soul</i>

41:19.145 --> 41:20.146
That's good.

41:20.313 --> 41:23.191
<i>In black and white</i>

41:23.274 --> 41:26.820
<i>They really, really ought to know</i>

41:26.903 --> 41:28.446
OK, really belt it out this time.

41:28.530 --> 41:32.534
And can we hear the Ts, please?
Enunciate. T-t-t.

41:33.159 --> 41:34.452
<i>You shouldn't have to...</i>

41:34.536 --> 41:38.456
<i>Shout, shout, let it all out</i>

41:38.540 --> 41:42.252
<i>These are the things
I can do without</i>

41:42.335 --> 41:43.712
<i>Come on</i>

41:43.795 --> 41:44.796
Lisa?

41:44.879 --> 41:47.590
<i>I'm talking to you, come on</i>

41:47.674 --> 41:49.426
Look, I understand
you want them to be passionate

41:49.509 --> 41:52.262
but really,
it just doesn't sound very good.

41:52.512 --> 41:56.516
They're having fun. Better that
than sounding joyless and in tune.

41:56.599 --> 42:00.603
I don't think projection is our issue.
All the top conductors...

42:00.687 --> 42:03.023
This reminds me of
when my parents got divorced.

42:44.022 --> 42:45.607
Have you got first-aid kit, Crooks?

42:46.399 --> 42:48.443
What's the problem?
I'm the designated first-aider.

42:48.526 --> 42:50.779
Honestly, it's fine.
I just need some plasters.

42:50.862 --> 42:53.782
I'll be the judge of that.
There's nothing I didn't see in Iraq.

42:58.912 --> 43:00.413
It's for Dawn's nipples.

43:01.831 --> 43:03.625
She forgot to wear a bra
and they're chafing.

43:05.335 --> 43:08.213
Erm... you'll find
some plasters in there.

43:08.296 --> 43:10.799
Yeah, I'll bring... Yeah.

43:18.264 --> 43:19.891
Aa-ooh!

43:23.353 --> 43:24.896
<i>Ooh, ooh</i>

43:24.979 --> 43:26.356
Sounds really nice.

43:27.399 --> 43:29.234
That sounds gorgeous!

43:32.487 --> 43:33.655
Keep going, keep going.

43:33.738 --> 43:36.241
<i>Looking from the window above</i>

43:36.324 --> 43:38.326
<i>Like a story of love</i>

43:38.410 --> 43:39.536
- Go on!
- Go on.

43:40.078 --> 43:43.206
<i>Can you hear me?</i>

43:43.289 --> 43:45.875
<i>Came back only yesterday</i>

43:45.959 --> 43:48.753
<i>I'm moving further away</i>

43:49.713 --> 43:53.008
<i>Want you near me</i>

43:53.758 --> 43:57.387
<i>All I needed was the love you gave</i>

43:58.722 --> 44:02.475
<i>All I needed for another day</i>

44:02.892 --> 44:06.354
<i>And all I ever knew</i>

44:06.938 --> 44:07.981
<i>Only you</i>

44:08.064 --> 44:10.233
<i>Ba-da-da, bum-bum</i>

44:10.316 --> 44:12.819
<i>Ba-da-da, bum-bum</i>

44:12.902 --> 44:15.947
<i>Sometimes when I
think of her name</i>

44:16.031 --> 44:18.992
<i>When it's only a game</i>

44:19.701 --> 44:22.871
<i>And I need you</i>

44:23.163 --> 44:26.124
<i>Listen to the words that you say...</i>

44:27.709 --> 44:30.253
Go on, Jess.

44:30.337 --> 44:32.172
Bravo!

44:33.673 --> 44:35.091
Fifty quid a ticket, mate.

44:36.426 --> 44:38.428
Where are you going?
Where were you hiding that?

44:40.930 --> 44:43.058
Of course the Welsh girl
can bloody sing.

44:43.141 --> 44:44.559
It's all that yodelling
in the valleys.

44:44.642 --> 44:46.644
Thank you, kind ramblers!

44:46.728 --> 44:49.522
<i>All of the people,
around us they say</i>

44:49.606 --> 44:50.648
I don't know.

44:51.483 --> 44:53.902
Maybe this choir isn't about
singing for ourselves

44:54.819 --> 44:56.529
You know, maybe it's about them
being heard.

44:59.449 --> 45:00.909
Are you suggesting a performance?

45:00.992 --> 45:02.994
Yeah, but, you know, nothing fancy.

45:03.536 --> 45:04.829
Just maybe going to town.

45:05.663 --> 45:06.956
People round here
don't know we exist.

45:07.040 --> 45:09.542
But the Military don't want us
to be tall poppies.

45:10.043 --> 45:12.212
- I don't know what that means.
- It means...

45:12.462 --> 45:13.963
It's about appropriateness.

45:14.506 --> 45:18.468
I'm sure between us we can
figure out something appropriate.

45:19.052 --> 45:20.303
That's amazing.

45:20.387 --> 45:22.555
In the market with
everyone watching?

45:22.639 --> 45:23.848
It ticks a box, apparently.

45:23.932 --> 45:26.142
The new community covenant
to break down barriers

45:26.226 --> 45:27.394
and engage with the locals.

45:27.477 --> 45:28.728
Can we do Lulu?

45:29.187 --> 45:32.273
What about something modern,
like Rihanna?

45:32.357 --> 45:35.360
- <i>Africa</i> by Toto.
- No, we need <i>Holding Out For A Hero.</i>

45:35.443 --> 45:38.071
- That's a classic.
- No, it has to be something serious.

45:38.154 --> 45:39.864
Bonnie Tyler's got
really serious hair.

45:40.365 --> 45:42.909
- Emotional serious.
- <i>Time After Time,</i> Cyndi Lauper.

45:43.284 --> 45:44.661
I don't think I could do a sad song.

45:44.869 --> 45:47.706
Just sing the tune. Don't think about
the meaning of the words.

45:47.789 --> 45:48.915
Can I do a solo?

45:51.042 --> 45:52.752
I promise I won't lose my nerve.

45:52.836 --> 45:54.504
Mm-hm. Erm...

45:55.422 --> 45:57.924
or, we were actually
thinking about...

45:59.551 --> 46:00.593
missus there.

46:02.554 --> 46:03.555
No way.

46:04.806 --> 46:06.474
- What? Why?
- No, I can't.

46:06.558 --> 46:09.394
You can.

46:09.477 --> 46:10.562
- You can.
- You can.

46:14.566 --> 46:17.027
One, two, three, four...

46:17.110 --> 46:19.237
<i>Lying in my bed</i>

46:19.320 --> 46:21.406
<i>I hear the clock tick</i>

46:21.489 --> 46:23.783
<i>And I think of you</i>

46:23.867 --> 46:27.120
<i>Caught up in circles</i>

46:27.203 --> 46:30.832
<i>Confusion is nothing new</i>

46:31.291 --> 46:35.045
<i>Secrets stolen</i>

46:35.795 --> 46:38.381
<i>From deep inside</i>

